</p>
<p>The tone and content of your message should reflect your relationship with the deceased and their family.  While brevity is acceptable, sincerity is paramount.  A heartfelt message, even a short one, can provide solace in a time of immense sadness. Always prioritize genuine emotion over formality;  a simple, honest expression of sympathy carries more weight than a lengthy, impersonal message.</p>
    

